headline: Eastman Chemical price target lowered to $115 from $123 at UBS
summary: UBS analyst Joshua Spector lowered the firm’s price target on Eastman Chemical (EMN) to $115 from $123 and keeps a Buy rating on the shares. The firm sees another challenging earnings cycle, with “largely ok” downstream earnings, while upstream/commodity earnings will be impacted by higher costs and likely weaker end of quarter demand, the analyst tells investors in a research note. UBS sees earnings misses to drive stocks down vs. provide relief. Published first on TheFly – the ultimate source

headline: ClearBridge Mid Cap Portfolios Q4 2024 Commentary
summary: The fourth quarter proved a tumultuous one for mid-cap stocks. The return to large-cap and AI-beneficiary leadership was reminiscent of what we saw for a majority of 2024.
